# magiclists

Vanilla JS ES modules + plain CSS. Client-only; data via `js/api.js` → localStorage. Entry: `index.html` → `js/app.js`. No React/TS/bundler unless asked.

**Architecture:** `app.js` orchestrates; modules use `window` CustomEvents (`namespace:action`); item CRUD through `API` only. Tools: `js/tools/*.js` with `@tool` header + `init(mount)`; run `node scripts/build-tools-list.mjs` after tool changes. Board views: grid + freeform only (columns view removed).

**Before editing:** grep/read existing patterns in the area you touch and its callers. Minimal diff; no dead code or half-migrations. Reuse `CARD_ICONS` / `ACTION_ICONS` from `ui.js`.

**Design:** Minimal, lightweight, smooth, modern, compact. Dark default; use CSS variables and existing theme pickers. Reuse classes (`.btn`, `.card-act`, `.collapsable-*`, `.overlay`) — ask before inventing new ones. Modular files; same tropes across tiles, editor, sidebar, tools. Match existing interaction patterns (hover, overlay, persistent). UX first.

**CSS map** (load order in `index.html`; edit the smallest owning file):

| File | Owns | Primary JS |
|------|------|------------|
| `css/base.css` | `:root` tokens, tile/grid vars, `.is-hidden` | `gridDensity.js`, `tileFootprint.js`, `appTheme.js` |
| `css/shell.css` | workspace shell, file cabinet, FAB, `.btn`, display options, note footer/editor typography | `hamburger.js`, `displayOptions.js`, `ui.js` |
| `css/sidebar.css` | side panel, search, notes list, control bar | `hamburger.js`, `searchBar.js` |
| `css/cards.css` | `#app-canvas`, `.mini-card*`, color picker, custom backgrounds | `ui.js`, `colorPicker.js`, `cardTheme.js` |
| `css/overlays.css` | `.overlay`, `.modal`, `.collapsable-*` | `editor.js`, `editorModalChrome.js` |
| `css/board.css` | grid/freeform board, clock, drag/resize | `dragdrop.js`, `clockStyle.js`, `desktopZoom.js` |
| `css/themes.css` | `html[data-app-theme]` overrides | `appTheme.js`, `themePicker.js` |
| `css/drawing.css` | magicCanvas toolbar | `drawingBoard.js`, `drawingToolbarMenu.js` |
| `css/tools.css` + per-tool files | tool panels, calendar, sudoku, cosmos, radio, tv | `js/tools/*.js`, `sidebarRadio.js`, `sidebarTv.js` |

Grep sibling CSS files before adding cross-cutting selectors.

**Note footer:** `.editor-meta-wrap` → `.editor-meta-row--footer.editor-meta-row--inline`. One CSS block in `shell.css`; single-line `0.48rem` × `--note-font-scale`. Do not add per-view font-size overrides unless user explicitly asks.

**Deliver:** concise, no preamble; audit shared styles/components for regressions across board, editor, sidebar, calendar, tools.

## Git / GitHub (required — magiclists workspace only)

This section applies only in chats opened for this repo. Do not use this commit prompt in other projects.

Never commit or push unless the user explicitly agrees.

**End-of-turn commit prompt — mandatory:** If this conversation turn created or modified any project files, the assistant's final lines MUST ask whether to commit. Do not skip this when wrapping up, summarizing, or saying work is done. Do not commit silently.

Prompt format (last thing in the message):
1. One-line summary of what changed
2. Ask: **commit only**, **commit + push to origin**, or **skip**?

Skip the prompt only when the turn was read-only (no file edits) or the user already answered for the current changes.

When the user agrees to commit:
1. `git status` + `git diff` to verify scope
2. Stage only relevant files (never `.env`, credentials, or accidental junk)
3. Commit with a concise message (why, not a file list) matching recent repo style
4. Push only if they also want push (or ask again after commit)

If push fails (auth, hook, conflict), report the error and fix or ask before continuing. Do not force-push to `main`.
